			</classificationInformation>
			<sumFormula>Not provided</sumFormula>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Ion-adsorbed rare earth deposits are a critical component in manufacturing various products for green technology. They are formed through the weathering profile of rare earth elements (REEs), the potential of clay minerals in adsorbing REEs, and the ion-exchange mechanism. Ionic clays represent a sustainable type of rare earth element deposit, being non-radioactive and having a low CAPEX requirement. The leaching effect of an ion-absorbed rare earth ore can be enhanced by ameliorating the seepage effect with sodium dodecyl sulfate surfactant.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">离子吸附型稀土矿床是制造各种绿色技术产品的重要组成部分。它们是通过稀土元素 (REE) 的风化剖面、粘土矿物吸附稀土元素的潜力以及离子交换机制形成的。离子粘土是一种可持续的稀土元素矿藏，无放射性，资本支出要求低。利用十二烷基硫酸钠表面活性剂改善渗流效果，可增强离子吸附型稀土矿的浸出效果。</common:generalComment>
